	(71, "SNES, Game, Action Adventure", "RG9ua2V5IEtvbmcgQ2;RG9ua2V5IEtvbmcgQ29;RG9ua2V5IEtvbmcgQ291;RG9ua2V5IEtvbmcgQ291b", "Donkey Kong Country 3 - Snes Game", "Original Super Nintendo SNES game cartridge only. ", "Game", 1955, "Used"),
	(72, "N64, Game, Action Adventure", "QmFuam;QmFuam8", "Banjo Tooie - N64 Game", "The direct sequel to Banjo Kazooie for the Nintendo 64 took everything that was great about the original smash hit and built upon it. With 8 enormous, interconnected realms to explore, widescreen support, dynamic Dolby surround sound, and rumble pak compatibility the world of Banjo Tooie came to life like no other game before it. It’s hard to overstate just how massive Banjo Tooie really is. So let’s just say that the game’s 9 transformations and ability to play independently as Banjo, Kazooie, or the magical Mumbo were all vital to exploring every inch of this Rare masterpiece. The amount of content packed into this game is staggering: Tooie had more bosses than ever before. It contained a ludicrous number of collectibles, including 90 jiggies. There were over a dozen addictive minigames, and a complete family-friendly first person shooter mode where you used Kazooie to shoot eggs at your opponents. Banjo Tooie is a technical marvel that easily lives up to its predecessor’s reputation, and may well be the most fun ever crammed into a single N64 cartridge.", "Game", 5869, "Used"),
